{
  "doc_id": "9787",
  "text": "S. aureus ␣-toxin, a 33.2-kDa polypeptide encoded by hla, has recently been reported to be a key factor in the phagosomal escape of S. aureus in CFT-1 cells, a human cystic fibrosis airway epithelial cell line [CITATION_1] . Secreted as a water-soluble monomer, ␣-toxin assembles on cell membranes to form a water-filled pore, thus unfolding cytotoxic, hemolytic, and dermonecrotic activities [CITATION_2] .",
